  "prompt": "How much does it cost to learn at Oxford aviation academy?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, tuition fees and costs for training at Oxford Aviation Academy (now part of Oxford Saudia) can vary greatly depending on the specific course or program you choose. For example, the costs associated with a commercial pilot license (CPL) or an integrated airline transport pilot license (ATPL) program can range significantly.\n\nOn average, you might expect tuition fees to be in the range of \u00a350,000 to \u00a3100,000 or more for complete training, including ground school and flight hours. Additionally, there may be other costs such as accommodation, equipment, and living expenses to consider.\n\nFor exact pricing and details on the specific program you are interested in, it's best to contact the academy directly or visit their official website for the most up-to-date information.",
